cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image segmentation using convolutional neural networks. The use of pyramid pooling and focal loss also suggests that it may fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of neural networks for medical image analysis may also place it under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the mention of CT scans suggests that it may also fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
